cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper deals with the synthesis of FDG-PET scans from MRI scans using a deep learning approach. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image synthesis and analysis. The use of a 3D U-Net architecture for the synthesis task suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves the use of a deep neural network. The paper also deals with the classification of Alzheimer's disease, which is a common application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in medical imaging. The use of quantitative metrics such as MAE, PSNR, and SSIM suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of neural networks and learning (cs.NE) as these metrics are commonly used to evaluate the performance of deep learning models. Finally, the paper deals with multi-modal analysis, which is a common application of multimedia (cs.MM) in medical imaging.
